losed_at":"2025-09-16T13:53:54Z","author_association":"NONE","type":{"id":25076157,"node_id":"IT_kwDOAOSnPM4BfqG9","name":"Documentation","description":"An issue related to documentation","color":"orange","created_at":"2025-01-16T18:30:16Z","updated_at":"2025-01-16T18:30:45Z","is_enabled":true},"active_lock_reason":"resolved","sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### What is the documentation issue?\n\n**Issue**\nCurrently, the official Next.js examples are using long relative imports such as:\n`import { i18n, type Locale } from \"../../../i18n-config\";`\n\nThis makes the code less readable and harder to maintain, especially as nesting grows. \n\nNext.js supports [module path aliases](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/getting-started/installation#set-up-absolute-imports-and-module-path-aliases) via `jsconfig.json` or `tsconfig.json`. Using that, the same import could look like:\n`import { i18n, type Locale } from \"@/i18n-config\";`\n\n\n\n### Is there any context that might help us understand?\n\n**Proposal**\n- Update the examples to use the `@/` alias (which points to the src or project root) instead of deeply nested relative imports\n- Add `\n\"paths\": {\n      \"@/*\": [\"./*\"]\n    }\n` to `tsconfig.json` / `jsconfig.json` to each example \n\n**Why**\n- Improves readability.\n- Reduces risk of mistakes when reorganizing folders.\n- Aligns with how many production-grade Next.js apps are set up.\n\n**Question**\nIs Vercel or Nextjs open to a PR introducing `@/` imports to the examples?\n\n### Does the docs page already exist? Please link to it.\n\nhttps://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/examples/i18n-routing/app/[lang]/components/locale-switcher.tsx","closed_by":{"login":"icyJoseph","id":21013447,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIxMDEzNDQ3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/21013447?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"http